oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Newspaper photograph of World War I veterans from Blount County
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This photograph from the Maryville-Alcoa Times in 1968 has the caption "These draftees left 51 years ago today." The original photograph was taken on April 25, 1917, and shows more than two dozen Blount County men who left for Ft. Jackson, South Carolina for training to serve in the army during World War I. The caption identifies most of the soldiers.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: World War, 1914-1918; World War, 1914-1918 - History
